<figureCitation box="[650,729,1506,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. A – K" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,195,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,195,1745]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. A – K. Tugonia (Tugonia) huanghaiensis Xu, 1987. A – F, holotype, MBM no. 73 M- 030, length = 19.8 mm. A. Exterior of right valve. B. Exterior of left valve. Scale bar (A, B) = 2 mm. C. Hinge of left valve. Scale bar = 2 mm. D. Interior of right valve. E. Interior of left valve. Scale bar (D, E) = 2 mm. F. Close up of surface sculpture. Scale bar = 2 mm. G – K, paratype, MBM no. 57 M- 101, length = 16.2 mm. G. Exterior of right valve. H. Exterior of left valve. Scale bar (G, H) = 5 mm. I. Hinge of left valve. Scale bar = 2 mm. J. Interior of right valve. K. Interior of left valve. Scale bar (J, K) = 5 mm. L. Tugonia (Distugonia) decurtata (A. Adams, 1851). From Okutani (2000: pl. 508, fig. 4, with permission from author)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281740/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="53">
